The question is, why do so few
Scrum Masters progress to the PSN two

2
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:12,780
or the PSN three certification?

3
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:18,510
And ultimately it's
because they don't care, right?

4
00:00:18,510 --> 00:00:23,110
They didn't do it in order to
become better Scrum Masters

5
00:00:23,110 --> 00:00:29,060
or to understand the depth
and breadth of being a Scrum Master.

6
00:00:29,060 --> 00:00:32,360
Quite a lot of people do it
because they've either been told to do it,

7
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:34,170
right? Their
company has said,

8
00:00:34,170 --> 00:00:35,810
go take this class.

9
00:00:35,810 --> 00:00:36,540
Or

10
00:00:40,160 --> 00:00:42,700
they took the class
in order to get a certificate.

11
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:46,610
I always know who those people are,
because the first thing they ask is,

12
00:00:46,610 --> 00:00:49,640
"what happens with the exam?
What happens with the assessment?"

13
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:54,180
You know that that's all they care about.
They want the certificate

14
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:58,980
for a job interview or for
their professional development or

15
00:00:58,980 --> 00:01:01,460
whatever it is their company's doing.

16
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:06,520
And those are ultimately not people.

17
00:01:06,520 --> 00:01:07,740
They don't care.

18
00:01:07,740 --> 00:01:11,110
I read this blog post once.
It was absolutely fantastic.

19
00:01:11,110 --> 00:01:13,980
And it basically started with this phrase.

20
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:21,540
"If you're reading this, you're already
in the top 10% of all software engineers",

21
00:01:21,540 --> 00:01:22,660

22
00:01:22,660 --> 00:01:31,300
And what the author was getting at was
that there are so few people doing jobs

23
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:35,880
and work that they actually care about,
that they actually love,

24
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:39,770
that they're willing
to invest additional time,

25
00:01:39,770 --> 00:01:43,390
perhaps outside of work,
in going and reading content,

26
00:01:43,390 --> 00:01:47,080
on finding out what's going on,
on interacting with other people in

27
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:48,120
their profession

28
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:52,120
and learning more about it.
They just, I'm done with work.

29
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:54,260
We're done. I'll pick
it up tomorrow.

30
00:01:54,260 --> 00:01:57,430
And I'm only going to do these
with stuff within work time.

31
00:01:57,430 --> 00:02:04,160
And that's not
necessarily the type of person

32
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:09,920
